SIMPLE: phial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phial
<hw>Phi"al</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧"⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fiole</ets>, L. <ets>phiala</ets> a broad, flat, shallow cup or
bowl, Gr. <grk>fia`lh</grk>. cf. <er>Vial</er>.]</ety> <def>A glass
vessel or bottle, especially a small bottle for medicines; a
vial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Phial
<hw>Phi"al</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Phialed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Phialing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To put or keep in, or as in, a
phial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Its <qex>phial'd</qex> wrath may fate exhaust.</q>
<rj><qau>Shenstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philabeg</ent>⟦br⟧
